Okay, I understand. I need to identify and interact with elements on a webpage to maintain medical records, technical libraries, or correspondence files. This likely involves finding input fields for account information, amounts, and memos, as well as buttons to post or save the data. I will look for elements matching the given selectors and generate actions to fill them out and submit the form.

```json
[
  {"action": "check_if_exists", "selector": "input[name*=account i]"},
  {"action": "type", "selector": "input[name*=account i]", "value": "account_data"},
  {"action": "check_if_exists", "selector": "input[name*=amount i], input[type=number]"},
  {"action": "type", "selector": "input[name*=amount i], input[type=number]", "value": "100"},
  {"action": "check_if_exists", "selector": "textarea[name*=memo i]"},
  {"action": "type", "selector": "textarea[name*=memo i]", "value": "memo_text"},
  {"action": "check_if_exists", "selector": "button:has-text(\"post\" i), button:has-text(\"save\" i)"},
  {"action": "click", "selector": "button:has-text(\"post\" i), button:has-text(\"save\" i)"}
]
```
